A self-professed lifelong fan of [[professional wrestling]], Bad Bunny began making appearances in the American promotion [[WWE]] in 2021. During WWE's annual [[Royal Rumble (2021)|Royal Rumble]] event held on January 31, 2021,<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/bad-bunny-wwe-royal-rumble-1119136/|title=Bad Bunny to Perform Live at WWE Royal Rumble|date=January 26, 2021|last=Shaffer|first=Claire|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=February 26, 2021|archive-date=February 26, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226194959/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/bad-bunny-wwe-royal-rumble-1119136/|url-status=live}}</ref> Bad Bunny performed his song "Booker T" live, which also had an appearance by [[Booker T (wrestler)|the former wrestler of the same name]].<ref name="RR2021">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WWE Royal Rumble results: Powell's live review of the Royal Rumble matches, Drew McIntyre vs. Goldberg for the WWE Championship, Roman Reigns vs. Kevin Owens in a Last Man Standing match for the WWE Universal Championship, Sasha Banks vs. Carmella for the Smackdown Women's Championship|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2021/01/31/wwe-royal-rumble-results-powells-live-review-of-the-royal-rumble-matches-drew-mcintyre-vs-goldberg-for-the-wwe-championship-roman-reigns-vs-kevin-owens-in-a-last-man-standing-match-for-the-wwe/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=January 31, 2021|access-date=January 31, 2021|archive-date=February 1, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201000249/https://prowrestling.net/site/2021/01/31/wwe-royal-rumble-results-powells-live-review-of-the-royal-rumble-matches-drew-mcintyre-vs-goldberg-for-the-wwe-championship-roman-reigns-vs-kevin-owens-in-a-last-man-standing-match-for-the-wwe/|url-status=live}}</ref> He then began appearing on WWE's weekly television show, ''[[WWE Raw|Monday Night Raw]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/bad-bunny-wrestlemania-interview-9553574/amp/ |title=Wrestling with Bad Bunny: WWE Friends (And Foes) Sound off Ahead of His Wrestlemania Match |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=April 8, 2021 |access-date=February 11, 2022 |archive-date=February 11, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220211143326/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/bad-bunny-wrestlemania-interview-9553574/amp/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Wrestler [[Damian Priest]], a fellow Puerto Rican, allied with Bad Bunny and helped him win the [[WWE 24/7 Championship]] from [[Akira Tozawa]] on the February 15 episode of ''Raw''.<ref name="Raw02152021">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2021/02/15/2-15-wwe-raw-results-powells-live-review-of-drew-mcintyre-vs-sheamus-vs-aj-styles-vs-randy-orton-vs-the-miz-vs-jeff-hardy-in-a-gauntlet-match-to-enter-last-in-the-elimination-chamber-match-for/|title=2/15 WWE Raw Results: Powell's live review of Drew McIntyre vs. Sheamus vs. AJ Styles vs. Randy Orton vs. The Miz vs. Jeff Hardy in a gauntlet match to enter last in the Elimination Chamber match for the WWE Championship|date=February 15, 2021|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=February 15, 2021|archive-date=February 16, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210216012347/https://prowrestling.net/site/2021/02/15/2-15-wwe-raw-results-powells-live-review-of-drew-mcintyre-vs-sheamus-vs-aj-styles-vs-randy-orton-vs-the-miz-vs-jeff-hardy-in-a-gauntlet-match-to-enter-last-in-the-elimination-chamber-match-for/|url-status=live}}</ref> On the March 15 episode, he relinquished the 24/7 Championship to [[R-Truth]] in exchange for [["Stone Cold" Steve Austin]] memorabilia, ending his reign at 28 days.<ref name="Raw03152021">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|date=March 15, 2021|title=3/15 WWE Raw Results: Powell's live review Cedric Alexander and Shelton Benjamin vs. Kofi Kingston and Xavier Woods for the Raw Tag Titles, Riddle vs. Mustafa Ali for the U.S. Title, Raw Women's Champion Asuka vs. Shayna Baszler in a non-title match|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2021/03/15/3-15-wwe-raw-results-powells-live-review-cedric-alexander-and-shelton-benjamin-vs-kofi-kingston-and-xavier-woods-for-the-raw-tag-titles-riddle-vs-mustafa-ali-for-the-u-s-title-raw-womens-cha/|accessdate=March 15, 2021|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|archive-date=March 16, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210316000027/https://prowrestling.net/site/2021/03/15/3-15-wwe-raw-results-powells-live-review-cedric-alexander-and-shelton-benjamin-vs-kofi-kingston-and-xavier-woods-for-the-raw-tag-titles-riddle-vs-mustafa-ali-for-the-u-s-title-raw-womens-cha/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=24/7 Champion|url=https://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/24-7-championship|access-date=2021-09-24|website=WWE|language=en|archive-date=February 22, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210222025036/https://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/24-7-championship|url-status=live}}</ref> At [[WrestleMania 37]], Bad Bunny teamed with Damian Priest in a [[tag team match]] to defeat [[The Miz and John Morrison]] in his in-ring wrestling debut.<ref name="WM37N1">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WrestleMania 37 results: Powell's live review of night one featuring Sasha Banks vs. Bianca Belair for the Smackdown Women's Championship, Bobby Lashley vs. Drew McIntyre for the WWE Championship, Kofi Kingston and Xavier Woods vs. AJ Styles and Omos for the Raw Tag Titles, Bad Bunny and Damian Priest vs The Miz and John Morrison|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2021/04/10/wrestlemania-37-results-powells-live-review-of-night-one-featuring-sasha-banks-vs-bianca-belair-for-the-smackdown-womens-championship-bobby-lashley-vs-drew-mcintyre-for-the-wwe-championship-k/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=April 10, 2021|access-date=April 10, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411050550/https://prowrestling.net/site/2021/04/10/wrestlemania-37-results-powells-live-review-of-night-one-featuring-sasha-banks-vs-bianca-belair-for-the-smackdown-womens-championship-bobby-lashley-vs-drew-mcintyre-for-the-wwe-championship-k/|archive-date=April 11, 2021|url-status=live}}</ref>

At the [[Royal Rumble (2022)|2022 Royal Rumble]] on January 29, Bad Bunny returned to WWE, competing in the men's Royal Rumble match. He eliminated [[Sheamus]] and [[Dolph Ziggler]] and lasted until the final five, when he was eliminated by the eventual winner, [[Brock Lesnar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://comicbook.com/wwe/news/bad-bunny-returns-to-wwe-competes-in-the-2022-mens-royal-rumble/|title=Bad Bunny Returns to WWE, Competes in the 2022 Men's Royal Rumble|work=[[ComicBook.com]]|date=January 30, 2022 |access-date=February 1, 2022|archive-date=February 1, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220201032025/https://comicbook.com/wwe/news/bad-bunny-returns-to-wwe-competes-in-the-2022-mens-royal-rumble/|url-status=live}}</ref> On January 23, 2023, it was announced that Bad Bunny would be a playable wrestler in the ''[[WWE 2K23]]'' video game as a pre-order bonus.<ref>{{cite web |last=Scullion |first=Chris |date=January 23, 2023 |title=WWE 2K23 has been officially confirmed for a March release |url=https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/wwe-2k23-has-been-officially-confirmed-for-a-march-release/ |access-date=March 13, 2023 |website=[[Video Games Chronicle]] |language=en-GB |archive-date=March 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230313015752/https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/wwe-2k23-has-been-officially-confirmed-for-a-march-release/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

On March 8, 2023, it was announced that Bad Bunny would serve as the host for WWE's upcoming event, [[Backlash (2023)|Backlash]], taking place in his native Puerto Rico.<ref>{{cite web|date=March 8, 2023|work=[[WWE]]|url=https://www.wwe.com/article/bad-bunny-host-backlash-san-juan-puerto-rico-may-6-2023|title=Bad Bunny to host WWE Backlash in Puerto Rico|url-status=live|access-date=March 8, 2023|archive-date=March 8, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230308155759/https://www.wwe.com/article/bad-bunny-host-backlash-san-juan-puerto-rico-may-6-2023}}</ref> On April 1, 2023, Bad Bunny joined the Spanish announce team to commentate during the match between [[Rey Mysterio]] and [[Dominik Mysterio]] on Night 1 of [[WrestleMania 39]]. Bunny would intervene during the match, preventing Dominik from attacking Rey with a chain.<ref>{{cite web |date=April 1, 2023 |title=Bad Bunny Helps Rey Mysterio Crush Son, Dominik, At WrestleMania |url=https://www.tmz.com/2023/04/01/rey-mysterio-bad-bunny-wrestlemania-match-dominik/ |access-date=April 3, 2023 |website=TMZ |language=en |archive-date=April 2, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230402224816/https://www.tmz.com/2023/04/01/rey-mysterio-bad-bunny-wrestlemania-match-dominik/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Two nights later on ''Raw'', Bunny—who was seated front row as a fan—was attacked and chokeslammed through the announcers table by former partner Damian Priest, who was now a teammate of Dominik Mysterio in [[The Judgment Day]].<ref name="Raw04032023">{{cite web|last=Keller|first=Wade|title=4/3 WWE Raw results: Keller's report on the fallout from WrestleMania 39 including Cody's loss, Bad Bunny chokeslammed through table|url=https://www.pwtorch.com/site/2023/04/03/4-3-wwe-monday-night-raw-results-kellers-report-on-the-fallout-from-wrestlemania-39-including-cody-rhodess-loss/|date=April 3, 2023|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|access-date=April 4, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230404035637/https://www.pwtorch.com/site/2023/04/03/4-3-wwe-monday-night-raw-results-kellers-report-on-the-fallout-from-wrestlemania-39-including-cody-rhodess-loss/|archive-date=April 4, 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> On the April 24 episode, Bunny returned and attacked Priest with a [[kendo stick]], subsequently announcing that instead of hosting Backlash, he would be wrestling Priest in a [[Street Fight match|San Juan Street Fight]] at the event.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/wwe/story/_/id/36289370/bad-bunny-face-damian-priest-wwe-backlash|title=Bad Bunny to face Damian Priest in Street Fight at WWE Backlash|date=April 25, 2023|last=Raimondi|first=Marc|work=[[ESPN]]|access-date=April 27, 2023|archive-date=April 27, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230427003937/https://www.espn.com/wwe/story/_/id/36289370/bad-bunny-face-damian-priest-wwe-backlash|url-status=live}}</ref> On the May 5 episode of ''SmackDown'', Bunny helped the [[Latino World Order]] (LWO) save [[Rey Mysterio]] from an attack from The Judgment Day, leading to Mysterio giving Bunny an LWO t-shirt, signifying his addition to the group.<ref>{{cite web|last=Mahjouri|first=Shakiel|date=May 5, 2023|title=WWE SmackDown results, recap, grades: Bad Bunny, LWO stand tall in Puerto Rico ahead of Backlash|url=https://www.cbssports.com/wwe/news/wwe-smackdown-results-recap-grades-bad-bunny-lwo-stand-tall-in-puerto-rico-ahead-of-backlash/live/|access-date=May 6, 2023|work=[[CBSSports]]|archive-date=May 6, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230506120534/https://www.cbssports.com/wwe/news/wwe-smackdown-results-recap-grades-bad-bunny-lwo-stand-tall-in-puerto-rico-ahead-of-backlash/live/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="BB LWO">{{cite web|url=https://411mania.com/wrestling/bad-bunny-joins-latino-world-order-wwe-smackdown/|title=Bad Bunny Joins Latino World Order On WWE Smackdown|first=Jeremy|last=Thomas|date=May 5, 2023|access-date=May 6, 2023|work=411Mania|archive-date=May 6, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230506025942/https://411mania.com/wrestling/bad-bunny-joins-latino-world-order-wwe-smackdown/|url-status=live}}</ref> At Backlash on May 6, Bunny defeated Damian Priest in a San Juan Street Fight, to the admiration of his home fans.<ref name="Backlash2023">{{cite news|last=Keller|first=Wade|title=WWE Backlash Results (5/6/2023): Keller's full results, match analysis, star ratings for Cody vs. Lesnar, Bad Bunny vs. Priest, Usos & Solo vs. Sami & KO & Riddle|url=https://www.pwtorch.com/site/2023/05/06/wwe-backlash-results-5-6-2023-kellers-full-results-match-analysis-star-ratings-for-cody-vs-lesnar-bad-bunny-vs-priest-usos-solo-vs-sami-ko-riddle/|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=May 6, 2023|access-date=May 6, 2023|archive-date=May 7, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230507002427/https://www.pwtorch.com/site/2023/05/06/wwe-backlash-results-5-6-2023-kellers-full-results-match-analysis-star-ratings-for-cody-vs-lesnar-bad-bunny-vs-priest-usos-solo-vs-sami-ko-riddle/|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Championships and accomplishments ===
* '''[[WWE]]'''
