== Awards ==
{{Main article|List of awards and nominations received by Bad Bunny}}Throughout his career Bad Bunny has received nine nominations at the [[Grammy Awards]], winning three times for [[Best Latin Pop or Urban Album]] with ''YHLQMDLG'' ([[63rd Annual Grammy Awards|2021]]), [[Grammy Award for Best Música Urbana Album|Best Música Urbana Album]] for {{lang|es|[[El Último Tour Del Mundo]]}} ([[64th Annual Grammy Awards|2022]]) and ''[[Un Verano Sin Ti]]'' ([[65th Annual Grammy Awards|2023]]), and he earned eleven [[Latin Grammy Awards]] out of twenty-seven nominations. [[ASCAP Award|ASCAP Latin Awards]] recognized him as the Songwriter of the Year in 2020. Within the [[List of MTV award shows|MTV award shows]], Bad Bunny became the first non-English language artist to win the [[MTV Video Music Award for Artist of the Year]] in 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hopper |first=Alex |date=September 1, 2022 |title=Bad Bunny Makes History With VMA Artist of the Year Win |url=https://americansongwriter.com/bad-bunny-makes-history-with-vma-artist-of-the-year-win/ |access-date=August 26, 2023 |website=[[American Songwriter]] |language=en-US |archive-date=September 30, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230930194900/https://americansongwriter.com/bad-bunny-makes-history-with-vma-artist-of-the-year-win/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

